            <title>[LU-2204] Test failure on test suite sanity-quota test_35</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2204</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Keith Mannthey &amp;lt;keith@whamcloud.com&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/e83005fc-f84f-11e1-ba0e-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/e83005fc-f84f-11e1-ba0e-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test 35 fails with Error: &apos;clients environments are insane!&apos;.  It could be a few different things. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This appears to have happened before all the recent quota changes landed.   Likely this issue will not reproduce but I wanted to have a place holder for it while I retest the underlying patch submission &lt;/p&gt;</description>
